# config/domains.conf.example
#
# Copy this file to config/domains.conf and edit it, or let later phase scripts
# prompt for missing values during execution.
#
# This file defines the mail domains hosted by this server.
#
# Multiple domain usage notes:
# - PRIMARY_DOMAIN is the main reference domain used in examples and defaults.
# - DOMAINS is the complete space-separated list of mail domains hosted by the
#   server.
# - All domains listed here will later be used for DNS record generation,
#   DKIM key generation, virtual mailbox routing, and webmail guidance.
# - The same MAIL_HOSTNAME can serve many domains.
#
# Example:
#   PRIMARY_DOMAIN="example.com"
#   DOMAINS="example.com example.net example.org"
#
# In that example:
# - the server hostname may still be mail.example.com
# - users can have addresses in example.com, example.net, and example.org
# - the router and public IP settings remain host-based, not domain-based
#
PRIMARY_DOMAIN="example.com"
DOMAINS="example.com example.net example.org"
